                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="339146" author="adilger" created="Wed, 29 Jun 2022 15:34:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report Thomas.  It looks like this may already be addressed by patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/46836&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/46836&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;LU-15652 build: On Debian detect -common kernel headers

Check for a matching /usr/src/linux-headers-&amp;lt;ver&amp;gt;-common/
and update the --with-linux argument accordingly.

Also move LC_GLIBC_SUPPORT_COPY_FILE_RANGE outside
of utils as this also breaks the dkms build on Debian
with &apos;static&apos; follows &apos;non static&apos; declairation of
copy_file_range.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
